    {
      "id": "army_patrol_rule",
      "type": "rule_reminder",
      "title": "Army Patrol",
      "text": "During the scenario, the Nome Army patrols the kingdom.  At the start of the game, draw two cards from the Army Patrol Deck and place them to the left of the deck.  The leftmost card is referred to as the Active card.  It is considered to be in play and its effects active.  The other faceup card is the Next card.  This card is visible, but it is not considered to be in play, and its effects are not active."
    },
    {
      "id": "billinas_eggs",
      "text": "Put a copy of Billina's Eggs into play in each investigator's play area.  Remove each other copy of Billina's Eggs from the game."
    },
    {
      "id": "tunnels_end",
      "text": "Put the Tunnel's End and Royal Audience Chamber locations into play.  Randomly put four of the six Outer Kingdom locations and four of the six Inner Kingdom locations into play.  Remove each other copy of Outer Kingdom and Inner Kingdom from the game.  Each investigator begins play at Tunnel's End."
    },
    {
      "id": "nome_army",
      "text": "Put the Nome Army enemy into play next to the agenda deck."
    },
    {
      "id": "army_patrol",
      "text": "Shuffle the four Army Patrol story cards together to create the Army Patrol deck.  Set up the Army Patrol tableau according to the instructions on the next page."
    },
    {
      "id": "intro",
      "type": "story",
      "text": "The meeting adjourns and you immediately begin preparations for the difficult expedition.  Dorothy walks alongside you to tell you as much about the Nome Kingdom as she knows.  \"Ruggedo used to be the Nome King, back when we first went there to free the royal family of Ev, but his ol' steward Kaliko is Nome King now.  Though I can't reckon if he's in charge now that Ruggedo is back and filled up with the Colour's power.  But if they still act like Nomes at all, then I think we have a secret weapon.\"  Dorothy gives you a weary but confident look, and leads you to the palace gardens where you find a large yellow hen milling about, surrounded by her chicks.  \"Billina!\" Dorothy calls out, \"we've got to go to the Nome Kingdom again.  Do you think you can supply us?\"\nThe hen gives an irritated cluck, not bothering to look up from her chicks.  \"Isn't this Colour enough of a problem without the Nomes?  But yes, I can spare some eggs for the journey.  I'm surprised I'm still laying eggs at all with this uneasy air around us.\"  You look to Dorothy for context, but Billina continues with the same disgruntled tone.  \"Nomes are terrified of eggs.  Ozma said that eggs turn them mortal, but I haven't known a Nome long enough to know if it works.\"  The Nomes' inherent fear may or may not be strong enough to overcome the influence and control of the Colour, but in either case, you must use every advantage to its fullest.  You return to your preparations, wondering how best to proceed into a hostile country deep underground."
    },
    {
      "id": "check_general_guph_surrendered",
      "type": "branch",
      "condition": {
        "type": "campaign_log",
        "section": "campaign_notes",
        "id": "general_guph_surrendered",
        "options": [
          {
            "boolCondition": true,
            "steps": ["inside_information", "reveal_two_locations"]
          },
          {
            "boolCondition": false,
            "steps": ["unfamiliar_territory"]
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "inside_information",
      "type": "story",
      "title": "Inside Information",
      "text": "Prisoner though he is, Guph has no qualms about sharing details about the tunnel and its surrounding area.  His early departure from the kingdom gives you no indication of how the caverns have been affected by the Colour, but something is better than nothing it all."
    },
    {
      "id": "reveal_two_locations",
      "text": "When the game begins, choose any two Outer Kingdom locations and reveal them."
    },
    {
      "id": "unfamiliar_territory",
      "type": "story",
      "title": "Unfamiliar Territory",
      "text": "Ozma's magic painting can only show people, not general places, and unfortunately cannot help scout.  All you can do is trust your instincts and be cautious in the approach.  Enemies will be abundant in the Nome Kingdom, both soldiers of the kingdom and maddened thralls of the Colour."
    },
