      "id": "R1",
      "title": "Resolution 1",
      "text": "Beaten back by the fierce resistance of the Colour and the infected Nomes, you trudge slowly back through the tunnel toward Oz.  Your companions try to offer encouragement and begin to formulate plans of a second attack when a strong rumbling begins to shake the tunnel.  You brace yourself against the wall for the tremor to pass, but find another cause for concern.  The ambient glow of the Colour dims, leaving you in near pitch darkness.",
      "steps": [
        "ruggedos_fate_is_unknown",
        "resolution_4"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "R2",
      "title": "Resolution 2",
      "text": "Ruggedo cracks one eye open as you stand above him.  His body is growing brittle and ashen, and beginning to distort beyond a humanoid form.  \"You... can fight the Colour...\" he rasps, trying but failing to reach out toward you, \"Your mind... and your body... must be strong... Maybe even... strong enough... to avenge me...\" Ruggedo's face gives the suggestion of a proud smile before his features dissolve away.  The Nome's body crumbles and spills like a sand castle in the wind, leaving only a featureless pile.  Silence briefly dominates the throne room before motion stirs from beside the golden gong.  Kaliko -- the Nome King once again -- pushes himself to his feet with a dazed expression.  \"The maddening thing... it's gone!  Did you... destroy it?\"  You shake your head, looking about the audience chamber warily.  This was a blow against the Colour, but you'd be a fool to think it was over already.",
      "steps": [
        "ruggedo_crumbled_to_dust",
        "earn_1_xp_nome_king",
        "resolution_4"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "R3",
      "title": "Resolution 3",
      "text": "Ruggedo struggles upward with a pained groan.  The Nome is pale and haggard, and visibly straining to stay conscious, but undoubtedly alive.  He sits panting and shivering for nearly a minute before he can summon the strength to speak.  \"Is it gone...?  What happened...?\"  You can only guess the trauma that Ruggedo has suffered since he touched the meteor, so it's clear that now is not the time for a full explanation.  You assure him that he is free from the Colour, but tell him that the fight is far from over.  Ruggedo shakes his head weakly.  \"Of course not... I felt the hunger in that being... its desire to feed and drain... and multiply...\"  The throne room shakes violently, but to your astonishment, the vibrant hues suddenly drain away, leaving you in dim light.  The Nome steadies himself while Kaliko -- the reigning Nome King -- slowly rises from beside the gong.  Ruggedo is a valuable firsthand witness to the Colour, so you hoist the weakened Nome out of the throne for the trip back to Oz.  Kaliko is dazed and distant, but you assure him as best as possible that the Nomes are free from the Colour for now.",
